content:
A data pack is a collection of components and related functionality packaged for deployment between orgs. For example, you can use data packs to deploy functionality from a sandbox environment to a production environment.

You can save in a data pack any object listed in Supported Data Pack Object Types. 

When importing and exporting data, we recommend limiting the file size to 2 MB. If you get the error Unable to connect to server (transaction aborted: timeout), use a file that is 1.3 MB or smaller.

Manually created data packs are suitable for deploying small numbers of similar objects. However, to bulk-export complex corporate data such as products, use one of these tools:

IDX Workbench deploys objects and metadata between orgs or between orgs and Git repositories. 

The OmniStudio Build Tool creates data packs that preserve object relationships.

To simplify deployment of multiple related objects, combine data packs into multipacks.

You can import data packs of some older OmniStudio for Vlocity objects into an OmniStudio Standard org. Omnistudio Data Mapper, Integration Procedure, and LWC-enabled OmniScript objects are automatically converted to Salesforce standard objects.

Create a DataPack or a MultiPack by exporting DataPacks, which are files with a selected objectâ€™s data in JSON format. A single DataPack contains one main object and its dependent objects. A MultiPack is a DataPack that contains multiple main objects and their dependent objects.

Supported Data Pack Object Types lists the objects that can be exported as data packs.

Publish Data Packs to Connected Orgs by connecting two orgs and publishing data packs from the source org to a target that you configure as a Salesforce connected app.

To fix the error message No Configuration Found while trying to import or export a DataPack, update your Salesforce org configuration with code in Anonymous Apex.
title: Data Deployment with Data Packs
